(96, 1, '2021-05-03 12:03:08', '2021-05-03 09:03:08', '', 'Adam Branch', 'Dr Adam Branch (2024)\n\nAdam Branch is Reader in International Politics and the Director of the Centre of African Studies at the University of Cambridge. He received his PhD in political science from Columbia University and his BA from Harvard University. Prior to joining Cambridge, he was Senior Research Fellow at the Makerere Institute of Social Research in Kampala. Adam’s research broadly examines the politics of global justice interventions, in particular peacebuilding, international criminal law, and now sustainable energy and climate change mitigation, all with a regional focus on East Africa. He is author of two books, Displacing Human Rights and Africa Uprising: Popular Protest and Political Change (with Zachariah Mampilly). His research has been funded by the AHRC, GCRF, and the British Academy, and he is a series editor for African ', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'adam-branch-2024-485x500', '', '', '2021-05-03 12:14:57', '2021-05-03 09:14:57', '', 92, 'http://localhost/biea/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Adam-Branch-2024-485x500-1.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
